<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
1.6-1.9 mm long (mean = 1.76 mm; n = 5); 2.67-3.17
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the entire length of interstriae 2 unarmed by tubercles; posterolateral margin of elytra rounded, unarmed; declivital interstriae flat, interstriae 2 not impressed; and denticles on interstriae 1 and 3 small.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. huifenyinae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="huifenyinae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. huifenyinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is distinguished by the shiny declivity, posterolateral declivity margin rounded and unarmed and smaller denticles on interstriae 1 and 3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
